The Head Veterinary Surgeon of Ukraine has sent his resignation
-----------------------------------------------
Today [6 Dec 2005], Petro Verbytsky announced his resignation in the
parliamentary session. He also urged the government of Ukraine to sign it
as soon as possible.
As a reminder, the bird flu outbreak was provoked by a lack of preventive
measures. The 1st cases were registered 2 months ago, but the government
and the local authorities did not respond.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[If indeed the 1st Highly Pathogenic Avian Influenza (HPAI) cases in Crimea
were registered earlier (September? October? 2005), this will fill in a
missing link and complete the mapped trail of virus spread, from southern
Siberia to the Balkans: in July 2005 -- Novosibirsk; in August 2005 --
Altai Territory, Chelyabinsk region, Kurgan Region, Novosibirsk region,
Omsk region and Tiumen region; later in August 2005 -- Kalmykia (media
reports, no official confirmation; see item 3); in October 2005 -- Romania,
Turkey, Croatia. See BBC bird migration map, cited in 20051018.3041
<http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/4348404.stm#map>
and OIE outbreaks map at
<http://www.oie.int/cartes/RUS050826.jpg>.
The reporting of cases in wild swans in the Volga delta, Astrakhan (see
further item 3 and comments), is an additional piece of information to
support the (not yet unequivocally proven) likely assumption on the role of
migratory birds in the spread of H5N1 HPAI. - Mod.AS]
